         //////EXPRESS////
         Express.js is a Node js web application server framework, which is specifically designed for 
         building single-page, multi-page, and hybrid web applications.
         It has become the standard server framework for node.js. Express is the backend part 
         of something known as the MEAN stack.

         /////// ROUTERS ////
         Routing determine the way in which an application responds to a client request to a particular endpoint.

         For example, 
